Principal components analysis:

The PCA is also a bit strange: why the 48h samples are clustering away from the other 2 time-points?

Gene filtering

We traced back a gene with large fold change and it has 0 counts in all the three replica. This indicates that the preprocessing pipeline cannot handle genes with zero expression.

We don’t have access to the pipeline, so here we filter out genes that have zero counts in 2 out of the 3 replica in any condition (in the raw data).

How many genes we loose if we remove those who are not expressed in a condition? In the table: TRUE: remove; FALSE: keep.

# which genes to remove: 
# the ones that have n_positive <2 in at least 1 condition:
raw_count_stats <- raw_count_stats %>% 
    group_by(gene_ensembl_id) %>%
    summarise(to_remove = any(n_positive < 2)) 
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
raw_count_stats %>%
    pull(to_remove) %>% table() %>% print()
## .
## FALSE  TRUE 
## 16552 41843
keep_genes <- raw_count_stats %>% filter(!to_remove) %>% pull(gene_ensembl_id)

we would remove 41.8k genes and keep 16552.

filtered_transcript_data <- transcript_data %>% filter(ensembl_gene_id %in% keep_genes)

Now the boxplot looks much nicer:
